1. cs.IT (Information Theory) is the most likely category as the paper deals with the secrecy capacity of codes from an information-theoretic perspective. 
2. cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is also a likely category as the paper deals with the passive eavesdropper model and secrecy capacity. 
3. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is a possible category as the paper deals with minimum storage regenerating codes. 
4. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is a possible category as the paper deals with distributed storage systems. 
5. cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is a less likely category as the paper does not explicitly deal with computational complexity, but it may be relevant in some aspects of the analysis.
